National Security Advisor Jake Sullivan, Secretary of Defense Lloyd J. Austin III, and Chairman of the Joint Chiefs of Staff Gen. Mark A. Milley held a call with Ukrainian officials, including Head of the Office of the President Andriy Yermak, Minister of Defence Oleksii Reznikov, and Commander-in-Chief of the Ukrainian Armed Forces Gen. Valerii Zaluzhnyi. They discussed the ongoing conflict with Russia and reiterated the United States' support for Ukraine's armed forces. The Ukrainian officials provided an update on the battlefield conditions and expressed their gratitude for the continued provision of U.S. security assistance. President Volodymyr Zelenskyy of Ukraine joined the call towards the end.